         <div type="translation">
            <p>Imperator Caesar Trajanus to the Smyrnaeotes. I wish no one from the free cities to be forced into (performing) your liturgy, and especially no one from Aphrodisias, since that city has been removed from the <term lang="la">formula provinciae</term> so that it is not liable either to the common liturgies of Asia or to others. I release Tiberius Julianos Attalos from (performance of a liturgy in) the temple in Smyrna; (he is) a man who has the highest testimonials from his own city; and I have written about these matters to Julius Balbus, my friend and the proconsul.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>See <title>Aphrodisias and Rome</title>, 113-115.</p>
